James Caroll has reportedly died suddenly according to reports. He appeared as Mary Taylor’s friend Colin in Coronation Street earlier this year. The actor and entertainer was best known for playing Brian ‘Bumper’ Humphreys on the Channel 4 soap between 1988 and 1991. Tributes have since poured in for the on-screen star following the news of his death. He had previously been poorly with pneumonia in early 2020 but had since made a full recovery. Friends of the late actor are believed to have confirmed the news on Facebook today. More to follow... 